  "response": "A scam is a fraudulent or deceptive act designed to trick someone into giving money, personal information, or something else of value. Scams typically involve:\n\n1. Dishonest schemes to obtain money or valuable information\n2. False promises or misrepresentations\n3. Deliberate attempts to mislead or manipulate victims\n4. Illegal methods of obtaining financial or personal gain\n\nCommon types of scams include:\n- Phishing emails\n- Phone fraud\n- Investment fraud\n- Identity theft\n- Lottery or prize scams\n- Romance scams\n- Fake job offers\n\nScams aim to exploit people's trust, hopes, or vulnerabilities for financial or personal advantage.",
